**Property registration** is mandatory in India to transfer legal ownership. Total cost = Stamp duty + Registration fee + GST on under-construction property (1% affordable, 5% regular) + legal & documentation charges. In Mumbai, stamp duty (6%) + registration (1%) on a ₹1 crore flat = ₹7 lakh in upfront costs — often excluded in first-time buyer budgets.
